00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:28,634
Yes, I did.

254
00:16:28,734 --> 00:16:30,034
How?

255
00:16:30,234 --> 00:16:32,735
Wasn't the kid scared
at the patrol as well?

256
00:16:32,801 --> 00:16:34,849
I spoke to him by putting myself
in his shoes...

257
00:16:34,934 --> 00:16:37,401
...and approached him by
communing with his emotions.

258
00:16:37,501 --> 00:16:38,868
Then, he testified.

259
00:16:38,968 --> 00:16:41,335
Communing with emotions...

260
00:16:41,601 --> 00:16:44,268
How do you do that? Can you teach me?

261
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:53,401
Why were you scared of that guy?

262
00:16:53,467 --> 00:16:56,301
If you tell me, I'll punish him for you.

263
00:16:59,834 --> 00:17:01,234
Talking like a kid...

264
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,534
Can you ask the witness
like that at the court?

265
00:17:04,634 --> 00:17:05,701
Why would I do that?

266
00:17:05,801 --> 00:17:08,101
I can just call his guardian
or the child's psychologist.

267
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:09,001
My gosh.

268
00:17:09,701 --> 00:17:11,101
Mother, where should I put this?

269
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,701
Mother? Just call me as you used to.

270
00:17:14,234 --> 00:17:16,935
That's enough. You should all go to work.
Hurry up and go.

271
00:17:18,501 --> 00:17:20,768
-Okay.
-Thank you for the food.

272
00:17:21,334 --> 00:17:23,968
Go ahead, I'm going to sew a button on
before I leave.

273
00:17:31,534 --> 00:17:33,701
Mom, have you seen the sewing basket?

274
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:45,901
Why is this...

275
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:50,500
Hongjoo, Prosecutor Jung forgot his phone.

276
00:17:53,033 --> 00:17:55,300
Mom, why is this here?

277
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:02,101
Did you hide this on purpose?

278
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:03,768
Yes.

279
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,167
But... Why?

280
00:18:08,868 --> 00:18:12,602
By the way, the kid
really likes Santa Claus.

281
00:18:12,701 --> 00:18:15,801
He testified well when I told
him that I'm Santa's friend.

282
00:18:15,968 --> 00:18:16,802
Santa Claus?

283
00:18:16,901 --> 00:18:19,368
No, not Santa Clause, but Santa Grandpa.

284
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:22,948
I'm more like an anchor style.

285
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:24,600
I actually can't make sounds like that.

286
00:18:24,701 --> 00:18:26,249
Why can't you?

287
00:18:26,334 --> 00:18:28,901
My Robin, did you poo? Did it feel good?

288
00:18:28,968 --> 00:18:31,469
I can do it... Did you eat?

289
00:18:31,534 --> 00:18:32,768
Was it good?

290
00:18:33,634 --> 00:18:35,968
Seungwon is good. You can't do this?

291
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:37,434
Yes, not at all.

292
00:18:39,801 --> 00:18:40,769
My phone.

293
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:42,367
I think you left it inside.

294
00:18:44,234 --> 00:18:45,468
I'm seriously out of it.

295
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:50,834
He can do it.

296
00:18:50,934 --> 00:18:51,635
Really?

297
00:18:51,734 --> 00:18:53,867
He can perfectly do it.

298
00:18:55,234 --> 00:18:56,267
Tell me.

299
00:18:56,601 --> 00:18:58,202
Why are you so mean to
Jaechan these days?

300
00:18:58,534 --> 00:19:01,268
What did he do wrong
that you're so cold to him?

301
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:05,568
You said you met him at
the funeral 13 years ago.

302
00:19:05,934 --> 00:19:07,701
Are you okay when you see him?

303
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:09,268
I'm not.

304
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,767
I'm trying to forget about your dad...

305
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,334
...but whenever I see Prosecutor Jung,
he reminds me of that incident.

306
00:19:14,501 --> 00:19:16,202
I'm like this, but are you okay?

307
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,333
Yes, I'm fine.

308
00:19:19,434 --> 00:19:21,335
No, you're not fine.

309
00:19:21,601 --> 00:19:24,068
What did you say last time
when Prosecutor Jung passed out?

310
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:27,001
You said you
couldn't change anything...

311
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:31,934
...and was crying your eyes out in case
the same thing happened to him like Dad.

312
00:19:44,634 --> 00:19:47,667
Others may not know, but I know.

313
00:19:47,934 --> 00:19:50,535
I can tell what you're thinking of.

314
00:19:51,033 --> 00:19:53,667
Your dad passing away and
Prosecutor Jung's accident...

315
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:55,867
You're blaming yourself
and suffering from it.

316
00:19:56,234 --> 00:19:59,202
You're going to continue
to blame yourself and suffer...

317
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:00,801
And get hurt again...

318
00:20:00,934 --> 00:20:02,401
That's what you'll most probably do.

319
00:20:03,601 --> 00:20:04,569
Mom.

320
00:20:04,634 --> 00:20:09,435
I'm afraid that you'll get hurt
meeting Prosecutor Jung again...

321
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:11,133
I'm worried.

322
00:20:13,634 --> 00:20:14,535
So...

323
00:20:15,934 --> 00:20:16,868
Mom.

324
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:20,868
I'm really fine.

325
00:20:23,434 --> 00:20:25,501
I feel good thanks to him.

326
00:20:25,868 --> 00:20:27,769
I'm happy thanks to him.

327
00:20:29,434 --> 00:20:30,968
So, please don't do this.

328
00:20:32,834 --> 00:20:35,168
Please like him like how I do.

329
00:20:37,067 --> 00:20:38,301
Please be nice to him.

330
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:52,166
Hongjoo, have you seen my phone?

331
00:20:56,334 --> 00:20:57,768
Yes, here.

332
00:20:58,801 --> 00:21:01,568
You must be really out of it.

333
00:21:24,634 --> 00:21:26,968
13 years ago, to me...

334
00:21:27,968 --> 00:21:29,268
...you're a scar...

335
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:31,534
...and a wound to me.

336
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:35,834
I thought it'd be fine
if I just ignored it.

337
00:21:37,934 --> 00:21:42,001
But I guess I'm not fine
seeing how hurt I am.

338
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,067
Wow, the beach is so pretty here.

339
00:21:51,133 --> 00:21:53,067
I wonder if it'll look like
this if I took a picture.

340
00:21:58,434 --> 00:21:59,402
What's wrong?

341
00:21:59,501 --> 00:22:01,402
Are you worried about the trial today?

342
00:22:02,601 --> 00:22:06,085
No, I have a witness and autopsy results.

343
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:07,968
The witness is a five years old kid...

344
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:10,434
...and the autopsy result isn't clear
because of the organ transplant.

345
00:22:10,534 --> 00:22:13,968
True, but I have your
dream I can depend on.

346
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:18,201
You should still not be so careless.

347
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:19,867
Don't worry. I won't be.

348
00:22:19,934 --> 00:22:21,234
You shouldn't.

349
00:22:21,534 --> 00:22:22,667
If you do...

350
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:26,767
...I'm going to punish you.

351
00:22:41,234 --> 00:22:43,001
"Trial in process"

352
00:22:44,534 --> 00:22:46,101
We'll ask the witness.

353
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:55,200
Hello, Lim Seyong.
Can you hear me?

354
00:22:55,601 --> 00:22:56,402
Yes.

355
00:22:56,667 --> 00:22:58,967
A cop rescued you before, right?

356
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:03,001
Can you tell us what you told him
the other day?

357
00:23:05,434 --> 00:23:06,701
No.

358
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:11,434
He's so young.
How can he testify like that?

359
00:23:11,534 --> 00:23:14,634
Lim Seyong, you have to tell us...

360
00:23:14,934 --> 00:23:16,268
Mom.

361
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:23,034
It looks like it'll be difficult
to get his testimony...

362
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:25,334
We can try again after
he calms down a bit.

363
00:23:25,834 --> 00:23:28,668
We'll get back to the defense
attorney for the cross-examination.

364
00:23:28,767 --> 00:23:32,568
No, I think I can question now
since it's not regarding the accident.

365
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:33,900
Really?

366
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:36,667
Can the defense attorney
start the cross-examination?

367
00:23:38,801 --> 00:23:39,468
Sure.

368
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:56,767
It's really scary here, right?

369
00:23:57,033 --> 00:23:58,534
You must be wanting to go home.

370
00:23:59,000 --> 00:23:59,934
Yes.

371
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:02,467
What did you take to come here today?

372
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,601
The bus.

373
00:24:04,701 --> 00:24:05,801
Which bus?

374
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:08,301
I don't remember.

375
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:12,767
You can go home if you can
tell me which bus you took...

376
00:24:13,175 --> 00:24:14,400
You still don't remember?

377
00:24:14,968 --> 00:24:18,001
I remember.
It was bus number 6.

378
00:24:18,501 --> 00:24:20,469
Can Seyong's mother answer as well?

379
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,967
Did you take bus number 6 today?

380
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:26,419
No, we took number 433.

381
00:24:28,601 --> 00:24:31,601
Seyong, did you just lie?

382
00:24:31,667 --> 00:24:33,334
I don't know.

383
00:24:34,367 --> 00:24:36,400
How can the kid testify
when he's only five years old?

384
00:24:36,501 --> 00:24:37,302
That's all for me.

385
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,767
How can the kid testify?

386
00:24:47,367 --> 00:24:50,268
He's made the kid into a liar in seconds.

387
00:24:50,467 --> 00:24:51,701
He's our only witness...

388
00:24:51,801 --> 00:24:54,602
...but it's over if we impeach
the testimony like that.

389
00:24:56,434 --> 00:24:59,701
Prosecutor, will you do
any additional interrogation?

390
00:24:59,868 --> 00:25:00,502
Yes.

391
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:08,824
Your Honor, for communing with
the witness with his emotions...

392
00:25:08,901 --> 00:25:12,001
...I'll have to proceed without
having to use any law terms.

393
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,601
Sure, go ahead.

394
00:25:32,934 --> 00:25:34,835
Lim Seyong!

395
00:25:35,534 --> 00:25:40,301
I'm a friend of Santa Grandpa.
You know Santa Claus, right?

396
00:25:42,501 --> 00:25:45,735
Yes, but are you really his friend?

397
00:25:45,834 --> 00:25:48,497
This uniform is for Santa's friends...

398
00:25:48,567 --> 00:25:53,068
...and I can fly wearing this
uniform during Christmas.

399
00:25:54,167 --> 00:25:55,401
What is he doing?

400
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,801
Oh my gosh...

401
00:26:00,367 --> 00:26:01,801
Wow.

402
00:26:01,868 --> 00:26:05,602
You would never lie to
Santa Claus, would you?

403
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:06,834
No.

404
00:26:07,215 --> 00:26:09,849
Then, you wouldn't lie to me
since I'm Santa's friend...

405
00:26:09,934 --> 00:26:11,435
...and tell the truth, right?

406
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:13,934
Yes.

407
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,534
You drew this picture
before for the cop, right?

408
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:19,101
Yes.

409
00:26:19,167 --> 00:26:21,534
Wow. You did such a great job.

410
00:26:21,801 --> 00:26:25,135
Do you remember what
this man told this guy?

411
00:26:25,567 --> 00:26:27,401
Yes, I remember.

412
00:26:27,567 --> 00:26:30,401
Before I interrogate,
let's all hear from evidence number 67...

413
00:26:30,501 --> 00:26:34,369
...which was recorded on the victim's
phone and compare it to the testimony.

414
00:26:34,701 --> 00:26:37,268
Your Honor, if we hear the evidence now...

415
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:39,400
...the child may repeat it.

416
00:26:39,467 --> 00:26:42,001
No, maybe he already heard it.

417
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:45,400
We'll listen to the kid testifying first
and then listen to the evidence.

418
00:26:45,485 --> 00:26:48,467
And this recorded file was found
during the prosecutor's investigation...

419
00:26:48,534 --> 00:26:51,368
...and it'll be Seyong's
first time hearing this.

420
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:54,100
You may continue with interrogation.

421
00:26:55,701 --> 00:26:57,302
Now, Seyong...

422
00:26:57,901 --> 00:27:01,235
What did this man say to this guy?

423
00:27:02,701 --> 00:27:08,202
He pushed him and
asked him if he was drunk.

424
00:27:11,267 --> 00:27:12,749
Are you drunk?

425
00:27:12,834 --> 00:27:14,702
Your drunk behaviors cannot be forgiven!

426
00:27:17,567 --> 00:27:19,700
Then, what did this guy say?

427
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:22,834
He said he didn't need something.

428
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:27,200
And he said he learned
how to clean his shoes.

429
00:27:28,501 --> 00:27:30,135
I don't need to debut as a writer.

430
00:27:30,434 --> 00:27:32,335
I haven't learned anything besides
cleaning your shoes and cars.

431
00:27:32,434 --> 00:27:33,834
So what's the point of debuting?

432
00:27:34,467 --> 00:27:35,834
It's similar.

433
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:38,767
Now we have the witness's testimony...

434
00:27:38,868 --> 00:27:40,268
Now, the evidence on murder.

435
00:27:41,234 --> 00:27:44,102
We're almost done.

436
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,734
What happened to these two after that?

437
00:27:48,334 --> 00:27:52,935
The man in gray grabbed the other
guy's neck and pushed him.

438
00:27:53,601 --> 00:27:56,901
It made a loud noise and pushed him.

439
00:27:58,968 --> 00:28:01,068
How was the guy in the white?

440
00:28:01,501 --> 00:28:04,068
He suddenly fell asleep.

441
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,834
He fell asleep?

442
00:28:06,033 --> 00:28:10,033
So what did the man in gray do to
the guy in white who fell asleep?

443
00:28:11,067 --> 00:28:15,334
He pushed him down the elevator.

444
00:28:16,701 --> 00:28:18,768
He purposely pushed him down...

445
00:28:19,267 --> 00:28:20,001
That's done.

446
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,168
That's all.

447
00:28:27,801 --> 00:28:29,502
Santa's friend.

448
00:28:31,367 --> 00:28:32,567
So embarrassing.

449
00:28:35,501 --> 00:28:36,832
Walk slowly.

450
00:28:36,901 --> 00:28:39,034
You may actually end up flying.

451
00:28:39,868 --> 00:28:41,335
What is it?

452
00:28:42,601 --> 00:28:45,801
How did you pull of Santa Grandpa
with that personality of yours?

453
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,533
You're trying really hard.

454
00:28:51,133 --> 00:28:52,333
Of course.

455
00:28:52,934 --> 00:28:55,501
The accused is trying to get away...

456
00:28:55,601 --> 00:28:56,935
So, being Santa isn't a big deal.

457
00:28:57,467 --> 00:28:58,667
I can do more.

458
00:28:58,734 --> 00:28:59,767
What more?

459
00:29:00,234 --> 00:29:01,701
Can I see it next time?

460
00:29:01,801 --> 00:29:02,868
Of course...

461
00:29:03,367 --> 00:29:06,767
It's rare to have an autopsy and
organ transplant at the same time.

462
00:29:06,868 --> 00:29:08,102
There's a lot if you search for it.

463
00:29:08,167 --> 00:29:09,101
Did you search everywhere?

464
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,434
I did.

465
00:29:10,501 --> 00:29:11,233
I'm looking forward to it.

466
00:29:11,334 --> 00:29:12,768
Yes, go ahead.

467
00:29:25,033 --> 00:29:26,166
Welcome.

468
00:29:28,067 --> 00:29:29,501
Hey, Jung Seungwon.

469
00:29:30,901 --> 00:29:32,735
Myung Daegoo...

470
00:29:32,968 --> 00:29:34,135
You work here?

471
00:29:34,567 --> 00:29:35,600
You live around here?

472
00:29:35,701 --> 00:29:36,435
Yes.

473
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:41,296
Can I have 10ml trash bags
and food recycling bags in 2L?

474
00:29:41,367 --> 00:29:42,801
10 pieces each.

475
00:29:43,167 --> 00:29:44,601
Are you running errands for your mom?

476
00:29:44,901 --> 00:29:47,602
No, my parents passed away...

477
00:29:47,701 --> 00:29:51,402
...and I take care of the house since
my brother is the house destroyer.

478
00:29:51,601 --> 00:29:52,601
Charge me for this as well.

479
00:29:54,868 --> 00:29:57,302
Does your brother come here often?

480
00:29:57,400 --> 00:30:00,567
If a tall and normal-looking guy
who acts like a kid comes by...

481
00:30:00,667 --> 00:30:01,734
...that's my brother.

482
00:30:01,801 --> 00:30:02,702
Be careful.

483
00:30:05,133 --> 00:30:06,200
Hey, Seungwon...

484
00:30:06,968 --> 00:30:07,602
Yes?

485
00:30:07,834 --> 00:30:11,802
Can you ask your brother
to meet with my father?

486
00:30:12,434 --> 00:30:13,801
Your father?

487
00:30:13,901 --> 00:30:15,268
You should get closer to Seungwon.

488
00:30:15,367 --> 00:30:16,567
His brother is a prosecutor.

489
00:30:16,634 --> 00:30:17,535
Who knows?

490
00:30:17,634 --> 00:30:20,301
His brother may get your
father out of the prison.

491
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:23,734
Oh, about that...

492
00:30:24,601 --> 00:30:27,768
He's going through a lot because
of an important trial right now.

493
00:30:28,601 --> 00:30:30,402
I see.

494
00:30:32,234 --> 00:30:33,868
Then, just pretend you didn't
hear anything from me.

495
00:30:34,601 --> 00:30:35,735
I said something I shouldn't have.

496
00:30:40,801 --> 00:30:42,201
I'm home.

497
00:30:42,300 --> 00:30:43,168
You're home?

498
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:46,434
What's with the stool?

499
00:30:47,100 --> 00:30:49,334
I was putting it away since I thought
I wouldn't need this anymore.

500
00:30:49,734 --> 00:30:52,249
Then, we won't have enough
chairs for tomorrow's breakfast.

501
00:30:52,334 --> 00:30:54,434
Tell everyone to eat at their own homes.

502
00:30:54,834 --> 00:30:55,635
Why?

503
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:57,500
I'm tired.

504
00:31:00,767 --> 00:31:02,834
It's uncomfortable seeing Prosecutor Jung.

505
00:31:05,701 --> 00:31:06,734
Mom.

506
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,567
Mother, Mother, I peed on my own.

507
00:31:18,667 --> 00:31:20,201
The pee just came out.

508
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:21,433
Really?

509
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:25,067
Good job.

510
00:31:26,901 --> 00:31:29,835
I'm so proud of you, my prince.

511
00:31:32,167 --> 00:31:35,868
Grandma will be here in 30 minutes.
Can you stay here by yourself?

512
00:31:35,934 --> 00:31:36,601
Yes.

513
00:31:39,234 --> 00:31:44,901
Chanho, there's so many
people we need to be thankful for.

514
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:49,000
There's so many people
that we're indebted to.

515
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:51,434
Yes, we should hurry and repay
them back for their generosity.

516
00:31:51,501 --> 00:31:53,002
I'm fine now.

517
00:32:01,501 --> 00:32:02,668
