767
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:08,200
I don't think that's all going
to fit in the washing machine.

768
00:48:08,267 --> 00:48:10,634
I'm going to get it done
at the laundry place.

769
00:48:11,667 --> 00:48:12,501
Mom.

770
00:48:13,701 --> 00:48:15,734
Should I tell them not to come
tomorrow morning for breakfast again?

771
00:48:16,100 --> 00:48:16,901
Yes.

772
00:48:19,834 --> 00:48:23,568
Mom, I went to Jaechan's trial today.

773
00:48:25,467 --> 00:48:27,234
After seeing the trial...

774
00:48:27,334 --> 00:48:29,302
...I realized I've been
confused all this time.

775
00:48:31,267 --> 00:48:32,201
About what?

776
00:48:33,100 --> 00:48:39,133
Like you said, I thought
Dad died because of me.

777
00:48:39,767 --> 00:48:41,934
Jaechan was also
shot because of me...

778
00:48:43,934 --> 00:48:45,768
So, I was having a hard
time because of that...

779
00:48:47,467 --> 00:48:49,201
But I realized I was wrong
after watching that trial.

780
00:48:49,601 --> 00:48:51,402
I realized why I've been confused
all this time.

781
00:48:56,734 --> 00:48:59,201
Dad died because of
the soldier who ran away.

782
00:48:59,267 --> 00:49:01,800
Jaechan got shot because
Sookyung's father shot him.

783
00:49:02,868 --> 00:49:06,635
Those things would've happened in
those moments even if I wasn't there.

784
00:49:06,934 --> 00:49:07,735
Right?

785
00:49:08,701 --> 00:49:09,602
Yes.

786
00:49:11,434 --> 00:49:14,501
It was someone else's fault all along,
but I didn't know about it.

787
00:49:15,167 --> 00:49:17,001
I was confused for a long time.

788
00:49:21,133 --> 00:49:21,967
So...

789
00:49:22,834 --> 00:49:24,335
...do you feel better now?

790
00:49:24,634 --> 00:49:25,734
You don't blame yourself?

791
00:49:25,934 --> 00:49:27,435
No, I don't.

792
00:49:34,701 --> 00:49:37,435
Goodness. So much laundry to do.

793
00:49:43,056 --> 00:49:43,924
Mother.

794
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:46,834
I mean, madam.

795
00:49:46,934 --> 00:49:47,802
Hi.

796
00:49:48,300 --> 00:49:49,634
You're doing laundry?

797
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:50,734
Yes.

798
00:49:57,434 --> 00:50:00,101
Others may not know, but I know.

799
00:50:00,701 --> 00:50:03,168
Your Dad's death and
Prosecutor Jung getting shot...

800
00:50:03,267 --> 00:50:05,467
You're struggling because
you're blaming yourself for it.

801
00:50:06,501 --> 00:50:09,868
You're going to continue to
blame yourself, suffer...

802
00:50:09,934 --> 00:50:12,668
...and hurt yourself again and again.
That's what you'll probably do.

803
00:50:18,634 --> 00:50:19,634
Madam.

804
00:50:20,734 --> 00:50:22,034
There's something I'd like to say.

805
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,033
It's not Hongjoo's
fault that I got hurt.

806
00:50:26,534 --> 00:50:28,235
Someone else shot me.

807
00:50:28,801 --> 00:50:29,845
Hongjoo knows that's the truth, too.

808
00:50:29,934 --> 00:50:31,668
-So, she won't be confused about it.
-And she won't be confused about it?

809
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,100
And that she won't blame herself?

810
00:50:34,734 --> 00:50:36,101
How did you know?

811
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:38,800
Did you guys plan this together?

812
00:50:38,901 --> 00:50:41,568
Did you hear from Hongjoo
that I'd be here and followed me?

813
00:50:41,634 --> 00:50:42,335
No, not at all.

814
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:44,700
I just came here to do laundry
and happen to see you here...

815
00:50:44,767 --> 00:50:46,468
Don't talk nonsense.

816
00:50:46,567 --> 00:50:48,330
You don't do any chores and...

817
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:54,203
...yet you brought laundry here.
It's not natural at all.

818
00:50:54,300 --> 00:50:56,534
I do a lot of chores, Mother.

819
00:50:57,968 --> 00:50:58,758
No, madam.

820
00:50:58,834 --> 00:51:01,201
I'm sorry for telling you to do
it this way and the other way...

821
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,600
But you can just call me Mother.

822
00:51:10,934 --> 00:51:13,468
I'm sorry for being cold.

823
00:51:14,434 --> 00:51:16,834
I know I shouldn't be doing this...

824
00:51:16,934 --> 00:51:19,067
...but a person's heart can
be such a fickle thing.

825
00:51:20,067 --> 00:51:23,401
To protect my kid,
I'm hurting someone else's kid.

826
00:51:24,667 --> 00:51:26,601
I'm sorry for behaving
such a way as an adult.

827
00:51:29,567 --> 00:51:30,767
I'm really sorry.

828
00:51:33,167 --> 00:51:34,701
No, it's totally fine.

829
00:51:34,934 --> 00:51:37,701
Then, will you forgive me?

830
00:51:38,634 --> 00:51:39,667
Yes, Mother.

831
00:51:40,534 --> 00:51:44,513
Thanks for being so good
to her and taking care of her...

832
00:51:44,601 --> 00:51:46,935
No, I'm more thankful, Mother-in...

833
00:51:48,701 --> 00:51:49,968
No, Madam...

834
00:51:51,534 --> 00:51:52,468
Mother.

835
00:51:53,434 --> 00:51:54,268
Come here.

836
00:52:11,133 --> 00:52:12,400
It's a red car.

837
00:52:13,400 --> 00:52:15,001
Whose car is this?

838
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:23,433
That scared me.

839
00:52:23,534 --> 00:52:26,335
Prosecutor Jung, what are
you doing in front of my car?

840
00:52:26,567 --> 00:52:28,401
Is this your car?

841
00:52:28,467 --> 00:52:33,068
Yes, it's my car.

842
00:52:33,567 --> 00:52:37,001
Wow, this is my dream car, red car...

843
00:52:37,100 --> 00:52:41,034
Tell me anytime. I'll let you borrow it.

844
00:52:41,234 --> 00:52:42,035
Really?

845
00:52:42,100 --> 00:52:42,734
Yes.

846
00:52:42,901 --> 00:52:43,635
Why?

847
00:52:43,734 --> 00:52:47,668
I just checked and
Moon Taemin is charged.

848
00:52:48,367 --> 00:52:51,068
Guilty of murder!
Seven years in prison!

849
00:52:54,667 --> 00:52:56,568
He deserved
the maximum sentence of 10 years.

850
00:52:56,667 --> 00:52:58,268
Seven years is quite a lot.

851
00:52:59,100 --> 00:53:00,934
Good work. And...

852
00:53:02,868 --> 00:53:03,702
...thanks.

853
00:53:05,834 --> 00:53:07,268
You too?

854
00:53:07,667 --> 00:53:09,542
Why is everyone thanking me?

855
00:53:09,634 --> 00:53:12,934
Is a prosecutor doing his job
something to be thankful for?

856
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:17,367
Of course it is. But I'm just so thankful.

857
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:22,399
Yes. You said you'd let me
borrow it anytime, right?

858
00:53:22,501 --> 00:53:24,026
Yes, why?

859
00:53:24,100 --> 00:53:25,500
Then, now!

860
00:53:27,567 --> 00:53:28,234
Now?

861
00:53:28,334 --> 00:53:29,135
Wow.

862
00:53:29,734 --> 00:53:31,568
-Wow.
-Wow!

863
00:53:35,467 --> 00:53:36,168
The keys.

864
00:53:49,834 --> 00:53:51,034
Can you take your day off?

865
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:54,267
If we leave now, we can see the ocean
for about an hour and come back.

866
00:54:04,901 --> 00:54:06,968
It's the ocean!

867
00:54:21,934 --> 00:54:24,234
Wow, it's the ocean!

868
00:54:41,767 --> 00:54:44,282
It looks the same.
How did you find it?

869
00:54:44,367 --> 00:54:45,934
I searched everywhere.

870
00:54:46,133 --> 00:54:46,867
How is it?

871
00:54:46,968 --> 00:54:48,402
Is it the same as the ocean
you saw in your dream?

872
00:54:48,501 --> 00:54:49,701
Yes, it's the same.

873
00:54:50,234 --> 00:54:51,135
Lies.

874
00:54:53,000 --> 00:54:54,749
No, seriously.
It's the same.

875
00:54:54,834 --> 00:54:56,301
It's prettier than in my dream.

876
00:54:56,567 --> 00:54:59,001
You didn't have any dream.
I know you were lying.

877
00:55:01,300 --> 00:55:02,834
How did you know?

878
00:55:03,167 --> 00:55:06,300
I told you, right?
I'm a human lie detector.

879
00:55:06,400 --> 00:55:08,500
And I can tell you were lying.

880
00:55:08,634 --> 00:55:12,435
You kept telling me not to be careless
and you even came to see the trial.

881
00:55:12,968 --> 00:55:14,933
Your face made it obvious
that you were lying.

882
00:55:15,033 --> 00:55:17,345
Why didn't you say anything
even though you knew?

883
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:18,500
Why did we come here?

884
00:55:18,601 --> 00:55:20,668
I knew you wanted to.

885
00:55:21,934 --> 00:55:24,435
I can tell that you want me
to win the trial...

886
00:55:25,434 --> 00:55:26,901
...and come to see the ocean.

887
00:55:27,534 --> 00:55:28,634
I worked a bit for it.

888
00:55:29,834 --> 00:55:30,967
Actually, I worked a lot for it.

889
00:55:31,767 --> 00:55:34,067
Thanks for working really hard.

890
00:55:36,267 --> 00:55:37,300
You don't want to go in?

891
00:55:38,300 --> 00:55:40,433
It's too early.
I just want to watch.

892
00:55:40,901 --> 00:55:41,802
Okay.

893
00:55:55,601 --> 00:55:56,701
What a relief.

894
00:56:00,534 --> 00:56:02,534
It's not that cold.
Why don't you come?

895
00:56:02,634 --> 00:56:04,135
Stop lying.

896
00:56:04,334 --> 00:56:07,534
Your lips have turned purple
because you're cold.

897
00:56:08,033 --> 00:56:09,267
No.

898
00:56:09,701 --> 00:56:12,268
This picture is seriously
worth your profile picture.

899
00:56:12,734 --> 00:56:16,034
Really? Send it to me.

900
00:56:16,133 --> 00:56:19,266
Wow...

901
00:56:19,367 --> 00:56:21,500
How is this possible?

902
00:56:21,601 --> 00:56:23,935
Really? How did it come out?

903
00:56:24,734 --> 00:56:26,401
Let me see. Did it come out great?

904
00:56:26,501 --> 00:56:27,735
This is so fake.

905
00:56:29,534 --> 00:56:31,035
Wait.

906
00:56:31,801 --> 00:56:34,934
No! No!

907
00:56:35,033 --> 00:56:36,400
Stop!

908
00:56:38,934 --> 00:56:42,268
It's a blessing to know what's
going to happen in the future...

909
00:56:42,968 --> 00:56:44,635
That's what I used to think.

910
00:56:46,701 --> 00:56:50,635
But this blessing takes away
the feeling of butterflies in our stomach.

911
00:57:15,834 --> 00:57:17,468
It kills the will to challenge oneself.

912
00:57:17,534 --> 00:57:20,801
"My death, a rainy day, green umbrella,
SBC Blue Team Uniform"

913
00:57:20,868 --> 00:57:22,602
It puts out embers of hope.

914
00:57:23,767 --> 00:57:25,601
Today around 5 AM, a 52 year old man...

915
00:57:25,667 --> 00:57:29,101
...named Mr. Myung tied up
the underwear he was wearing...

916
00:57:29,167 --> 00:57:33,135
...and hung himself while serving
in Seoul Goomin Prison.

917
00:57:34,200 --> 00:57:35,639
A future I can't change.

918
00:57:35,734 --> 00:57:37,001
"A rainy day, green umbrella"

919
00:57:38,634 --> 00:57:40,168
A future that's been predestined.

920
00:57:42,067 --> 00:57:43,449
Father...

921
00:57:43,534 --> 00:57:46,168
In May 2015, Mr. Myung...

922
00:57:46,267 --> 00:57:49,734
...was pointed as the culprit of
a serial killing using injections...

923
00:57:49,801 --> 00:57:52,735
...that caused a stir and
was sentenced to life.

924
00:57:56,167 --> 00:57:58,267
That's another form of despair...

925
00:57:59,200 --> 00:58:01,233
...and makes me lose everything
by giving up...

926
00:58:01,634 --> 00:58:03,268
...and repeating every day in vain.

927
00:58:03,868 --> 00:58:05,335
Mr. Myung left a suicide note...

928
00:58:05,400 --> 00:58:10,001
...saying he was falsely accused
and that the truth must be revealed.

929
00:58:10,200 --> 00:58:13,400
Lieutenant Han,
is the walkie-talkie fully charged?

930
00:58:15,501 --> 00:58:16,335
It's...

931
00:58:22,734 --> 00:58:24,134
When did you start charging them?

932
00:58:25,167 --> 00:58:25,868
What?

933
00:58:28,100 --> 00:58:30,034
It's green. They're fully charged.

934
00:58:30,133 --> 00:58:31,433
Okay.

935
00:58:53,300 --> 00:58:55,600
I wish I gave her some time to
relax by bringing her to the ocean...

936
00:58:56,400 --> 00:58:58,634
...and that this can be a shelter
from those days that are in vain.

937
00:59:04,434 --> 00:59:05,268
I hope...

938
00:59:06,434 --> 00:59:08,068
you had an exciting day.

939
00:59:37,300 --> 00:59:39,168
"While You Were Sleeping"

940
00:59:39,267 --> 00:59:41,934
Are you saying that the cop may
also be dreaming of us as well?

941
00:59:42,033 --> 00:59:42,682
The person who killed himself...

942
00:59:42,767 --> 00:59:44,366
...in the prison is the same person
as the injection murderer.

943
00:59:44,467 --> 00:59:46,268
I'm going to interview
you guys starting today.

944
00:59:46,367 --> 00:59:47,068
Us?

945
00:59:47,167 --> 00:59:48,516
Can't you tell that they're lies?

946
00:59:48,601 --> 00:59:50,682
I'm just saying I'll check it myself.

947
00:59:50,767 --> 00:59:51,800
Hey, Prosecutor.

948
00:59:51,901 --> 00:59:53,602
There's something huge in there.

949
00:59:53,667 --> 00:59:55,168
-Victim...
-Victim?

950
00:59:55,267 --> 00:59:56,801
The injection murder case...

951
00:59:56,901 --> 00:59:57,901
That case...

952
00:59:58,000 --> 00:59:59,267
Answer me!

953
00:59:59,334 --> 01:00:01,434
He might be the accomplice
or the real culprit.

954
01:00:01,501 --> 01:00:02,935
The dream started.

955
01:00:03,033 --> 01:00:05,500
I see dreams of the person I saved.

956
01:00:11,467 --> 01:00:18,467
"While You Were Sleeping"
